<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Documentation ~ NodCord</title>
  <link rel="shortcut icon" href="/assets/img/logo.png" type="image/x-icon">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/assets/css/styles.css">
  <style>
    .main-container {
      display: flex;
      flex: 1;
    }

    .sidebar {
      width: 250px;
      background-color: #333;
      color: #fff;
      height: calc(100vh - 40px);
      position: sticky;
      top: 0;
      padding-top: 20px;
      box-shadow: 2px 0 5px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
    }

    .sidebar a {
      display: block;
      color: #fff;
      text-decoration: none;
      padding: 15px 20px;
      transition: background-color 0.3s;
    }

    .sidebar a:hover {
      background-color: #575757;
    }

    .sidebar a.active {
      background-color: #2fddfe;
      color: #000;
    }

    .content {
      flex-grow: 1;
      padding: 20px;
      overflow-y: auto;
      background-color: #fff;
      box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
      margin: 20px;
      border-radius: 8px;
    }

    h1, h2 {
      color: #333;
    }

    h1 {
      border-bottom: 2px solid #333;
      padding-bottom: 10px;
      margin-bottom: 20px;
    }

    h2 {
      border-bottom: 1px solid #333;
      padding-bottom: 5px;
      margin-bottom: 15px;
      margin-top: 30px;
    }

    p {
      line-height: 1.6;
      margin-bottom: 15px;
    }

    pre {
      background-color: #f4f4f4;
      padding: 15px;
      border-radius: 8px;
      overflow-x: auto;
    }

    code {
      background-color: #eaeaea;
      padding: 2px 4px;
      border-radius: 4px;
    }

    ul {
      list-style-type: disc;
      padding-left: 20px;
      margin-bottom: 15px;
    }

    ul ul {
      list-style-type: circle;
    }
  </style>
</head>

<body>
  <%- include('./partials/header'); %>
  <div class="main-container">
    <aside class="sidebar">
      <a href="#overview" id="nav-overview">Overview</a>
      <a href="#installation" id="nav-installation">Installation</a>
      <a href="#configuration" id="nav-configuration">Configuration</a>
      <a href="#usage" id="nav-usage">Usage</a>
      <a href="#api" id="nav-api">API Reference</a>
      <a href="#faq" id="nav-faq">FAQ</a>
      <a href="#contact" id="nav-contact">Contact</a>
    </aside>
    <main class="content">
      <section id="overview">
        <h1>Overview</h1>
        <p>Welcome to the NodCord documentation. NodCord is a versatile and powerful Discord bot framework that simplifies the process of creating and managing your own Discord bots.</p>
      </section>
      <section id="installation">
        <h2>Installation</h2>
        <p>To install NodCord, you need to have Node.js and npm installed on your system. Run the following command to install NodCord:</p>
        <pre><code>npm install nodcord</code></pre>
      </section>
      <section id="configuration">
        <h2>Configuration</h2>
        <p>After installation, you need to configure NodCord. Create a <code>.env</code> file in your project directory and add the following:</p>
        <pre><code>DISCORD_TOKEN=your_discord_token_here
BOT_PREFIX=!</code></pre>
      </section>
      <section id="usage">
        <h2>Usage</h2>
        <p>To start using NodCord, create an <code>index.js</code> file and add the following code:</p>
        <pre><code>const { Client, GatewayIntentBits } = require('nodcord');
const client = new Client({ intents: [GatewayIntentBits.Guilds, GatewayIntentBits.GuildMessages] });

client.on('ready', () => {
  console.log(`Logged in as ${client.user.tag}!`);
});

client.login(process.env.DISCORD_TOKEN);</code></pre>
      </section>
      <section id="api">
        <h2>API Reference</h2>
        <p>NodCord provides a comprehensive API for interacting with Discord. Here are some of the main methods:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><code>client.on(event, listener)</code> - Listens for a specific event.</li>
          <li><code>client.login(token)</code> - Logs in to Discord with the provided token.</li>
          <li><code>client.user.setActivity(activity)</code> - Sets the bot's activity status.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>
      <section id="faq">
        <h2>FAQ</h2>
        <p>Here are some frequently asked questions about NodCord:</p>
        <h3>What is NodCord?</h3>
        <p>NodCord is a framework for creating Discord bots with ease.</p>
        <h3>How do I install NodCord?</h3>
        <p>Run <code>npm install nodcord</code> to install NodCord.</p>
      </section>
      <section id="contact">
        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>If you have any questions, feel free to reach out to us at <a href="mailto:support@nodcord.com">support@nodcord.com</a>.</p>
      </section>
    </main>
  </div>
  <footer>
    <p>&copy; <%= new Date().getFullYear() %> <a href="/">NodCord</a>. Alle Rechte vorbehalten.</p>
  </footer>
</body>
<script src="assets/js/script.js"></script>
</html>
